  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BPRM; Integrated Preventative Health Care and Nutrition</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The humanitarian support to refugees from South Sudan is based on inter-agency response planning. ACF in the last two years has supported the establishment of nutrition programs in the two refugee host districts where there were none. Through the multiyear grant ACF will consolidate and build on experiences and lessons learned to strengthen the longer term capacity of the district health system to address current challenges and respond to the fluctuating needs arising within the sector. ACF will continue working within these districts to provide adapted social services reaching both refugees and host communities. ACF will aspire to reach the most vulnerable segments of the population through our strong community based program already established during the 2 years maximizing the potential of community based structures particularly the Village health teams and Mother to mother support groups to receive the targeted beneficiaries receive the curative and preventive care that they need.</narrative>
  </description>
